\par\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\sa360\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 By default, Scrivener will back up a project every time it is closed, and up to a maximum of five backups of each project will be kept around (with newer backups replacing older ones). You can change this behaviour and also choose the folder in which automatic backups are stored, as follows:}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\li763\fi-475\sa240\ql\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 <$Scr_Ps::1> \tab 1.\tab From the main menu, choose }{\f2\fs22\b1\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>File > Options...<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0  \tab 2.\tab Click on the \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Backup\u8221\'94 toolbar icon in the Options dialog that appears. <!$Scr_Ps::1>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\sa360\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 You will be presented with a number of options that allow you to determine when and how backups are made.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Click the \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Choose\u8230\'85\u8221\'94 button next to \u8220\'93Backup location\u8221\'94 to change the automatic backups folder, and click the \u8220\'93Open backup folder\u8230\'85\u8221\'94 button to open the folder currently used for backups in File Explorer.}
